==Quiz==

{{Quiz|question=1. Which of these countries border [[../Georgia|Georgia]]? |a=Greece. |b=Belarus. |c=Finland. |d=Armenia. |answer='''D''' - Armenia, Azerbaijan, Turkey and Russia border Georgia}}

{{Quiz|question=2. What's the capital of Portugal? |a=Minsk. |b=Lisbon. |c=Madrid. |d=Porta? |answer='''B''' Lisbon}}

{{Quiz|question=3. Which European country has the largest population? |a=Russia. |b=Turkey. |c=Germany. |d=United Kingdom. |answer='''A''' Russia}}

{{Quiz|question=4. In which country can you find Lake Bled? |a=Greece. |b=Sweden |c=Slovenia |d=Spain |answer='''C''' Slovenia}}

{{Quiz|question=5. In which country can you find Sagrada Familia? |a=Spain |b=Italy |c=France |d=Armenia |answer='''A''' Barcelona, Spain}}

{{Quiz|question=6. Which of these countries does not use the Euro? |a=Latvia |b=Greece |c=Finland |d=Poland |answer='''D''' Poland}}

{{Quiz|question=7. In which country can you find Frankfurt? |a=Italy |b=Germany |c=UK |d=Italy |answer='''B''' Germany}}

{{Quiz|question=8. How many countries are part of the European Union (as of 2014)? |a=15 |b=25 |c=28 |d=32 |answer='''C''' 28 countries}}

{{Quiz|question=9. Which is the smallest country in Europe (and the world)? |a=Kosovo |b=Monaco |c=Liechtenstein |d=Vatican City |answer='''D''' Vatican City}}

{{Quiz|question=10. Which country was divided in two during the Cold War? |a=Germany |b=Yugoslavia |c=Poland |d=Russia |answer='''A''' Germany: West Germany and East Germany}}

{{Quiz|question=11. In which country can you find Mostar Bridge? |a=Italy |b=Lithuania |c=Bosnia Herzegovina |d=Portugal |answer='''C''' Bosnia Herzegovina}}

{{Quiz|question=12. Which country became independent from the United Kingdom in 1922? |a=Scotland |b=Denmark |c=Iceland |d=Ireland |answer='''D''' Ireland}}

{{Quiz|question=13. Which country was first settled by Ingólfur Arnason in the 9th century? |a=Sweden |b=Finland |c=Iceland |d=Ireland | answer='''C''' Iceland}}

{{Quiz|question=14. Which Mediterranean country is divided into two parts: A Greek speaking part and a Turkish speaking part? |a=Cyprus |b=Montenegro |c=Albania |d=Malta | answer='''A''' Cyprus}}

{{Quiz|question=15. Which country lost 6 million people in World War 2? |a=France |b=Poland |c=Ukraine |d=Slovakia | answer='''B''' Poland}}

{{Quiz|question=16. Which of these countries is NOT a monarchy? |a=United Kingdom |b=Finland |c=Netherlands |d=Norway | answer='''B''' Finland}}

{{Quiz|question=17. In which European country can you find the World Heritage Site of Suomenlinna? |a=Finland |b=France |c=Switzerland |d=Slovakia | answer='''A''' Finland, in Helsinki}}

{{Quiz|question=18. Which country was bombed by NATO in the 1990s? |a=Cyprus |b=Russia |c=Belarus |d=Serbia | answer='''D''' Serbia}}

{{Quiz|question=19. Which of these countries was not part of the Soviet Union? |a=Kazakhstan |b=Belarus |c=Yugoslavia |d=Ukraine | answer='''C''' Yugoslavia}}

{{Quiz|question=20. Which country had a revolution in 2014? |a=Georgia |b=Cyprus |c=Ireland |d=Ukraine | answer='''D''' Ukraine, February 2014}}

