g)|Resource Management]] ==Given a scenario, distinguish and select the method or tool that is appropriate to conduct an [[w:Information_Technology_Security_Assessment|assessment]]== ===Tool type=== ====[[w:Port_scanner|Port scanners]]==== ====[[w:Vulnerability_scanner|Vulnerability scanners]]==== ====[[w:Protocol_analyzer|Protocol analyzer]]==== ====[[w:Port_mirroring|Switchport analyzer]]==== ====[[w:Network_enumerator|Network enumerator]]==== ====[[w:Password_cracker|Password cracker]]==== ====Fuzzer==== {{cite web|url=https://www.owasp.org/index.php/OWASP_Testing_Guide_Appendix_C:_Fuzz_Vectors|title=OWASP Testing Guide Appendix C: Fuzz Vectors|accessdate=2014JUN25}} ====HTTP – Hypertext Transfer Protocol interceptor==== {{cite web|http://portswigger.net/burp/Help/proxy_intercept.html|title=Intercepting Messages|accessdate=2014JUN25}} ====Attacking tools/frameworks==== {{cite web|http://www.networkworld.com/article/2168329/malware-cybercrime/black-hat--top-20-hack-attack-tools.html|title=Black Hat: Top 20 hack-attack tools|accessdate=2014JUN26}} ===Methods=== {{cite web|http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/columnist/komando/2013/07/19/hacker-attack-trojan-horse-drive-by-downloads-passwords/2518053/|title=5 ways hackers attack you (and how to counter them)|accessdate=2014JUN26}} ====[[w:Vulnerability_assessment|Vulnerability assessment]]==== ====[[w:Penetration_test|Penetration testing]]==== ====[[w:Black_box|Black box]]==== ====[[w:White-box_testing|White box]]==== ====[[w:Software_testing#Grey_box_testing|Grey Box]]==== ====[[w:Fingerprint_(computing)|Fingerprinting]]==== ====[[w:Code_review|Code review]]==== ====[[w:Social_engineering_(security)|Social engineering]]====
{{BookCat}}

{{AM&C-top}}
{{TRS-underconstruction}}
The new Trainz user is well advised to scout the bargain websites and Amazon.com's 3rd party partners and try to acquire various older Trainz releases. This is because the bundled content in a Trainz release varies quite a bit in the main, based on the routes bundled with the release, and there are many routes with dependencies on the DLS you may want to explore that will be calling for said assets. Further, many Auran coded assets fall into the category: "Not on the DLS", meaning if they were used in the many (more than 2,500) routes uploaded to the DLS, you are in the same state as looking for third party content that is not on the DLS: getting the hated '''Unknown asset''' error message in the {{TG|Task Completed}} pop-ups when finishing downloading in the DLH. Trainz stubbornly refuses to know about it's own published assets if the code hasn't been added to the DLS. Predicting whether it will be is much like 16th century weather forecasting-- look out a window and hope for the best.
==Handling Problems==
[[file:2014-0508 Running multiple Trainz versions-Identifying which Trainz TS12 loaded from a shortcut-method-1 (properties from TASK MANAGER-Apps Tab).png|thumb|One sure solution is open Task Manager using {{kp|SHFT|CTRL|ESC}} and select the {{kp|Processes TAB}}, find the [[TL\TADdaemon]] process and {{kp|LMB}}-click, then {{kp|RMBH+drag}} to Open File Location (Folder), which if you have your Windows titlebar set up as recommended to show your folder pathspecs, will reveal which folder copy is active.]] 
If you run more than one version of the same Trainz release, there is sometimes difficulty remembering which you launched. 
